Iger=E2=80=99s
Fubo Curveball, L.A.=E2=80=99s Political Fire, TV After Broadcast
-----------------------------------------------------------

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon digest of Puck=E2=80=99s
best new reporting.

Today, we lead with Eriq Gardner=E2=80=99s incisive summation of two legal =
dramas roiling the worlds of media and entertainment: The Times=E2=80=99 hi=
gh-profile copyright battle against Sam Altman=E2=80=99s OpenAI, and the Su=
preme Court=E2=80=99s imminent decision on the fate of TikTok. Will the soc=
ial media phenomenon survive the weekend?=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold:
Marion Maneker digs into an art world micro-scandal surrounding the estate =
of Peter Beard. Sarah Shapiro talks to Hill House Home boss Nell Diamond ab=
out the Pyrrhic success of the company=E2=80=99s category-defining Nap Dres=
s. Tara Palmeri and former Trump official Ken Cuccinelli debate the viabili=
ty of the next administration=E2=80=99s deportation strategy. And Julie Dav=
ich
chronicles a surprising development in the art brokerage business.=C2=A0

Meanwhile, on the podcasts: Democratic rising star Mallory McMorrow joins J=
ohn Heilemann on Impolitic to investigate a Trumpworld mystery. On The Vars=
ity, Sara Fischer joins John Ourand to contemplate the ripple effects of a =
TikTok ban on sports media. On The Town, Matt Belloni
connects with CBS Entertainment president Amy Reisenbach to envision the en=
d state of broadcast television. And on The Powers That Be, Dylan Byers and=
 Peter Hamby examine L.A. mayor Karen Bass=E2=80=99s bleak political future=
=2E=C2=A0

